Argentine Stocks: Mirgor Advances; Pampa Energia, Siderar Fall

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-02-21T20:36:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/argentine-stocks-mirgor-rises-steel-producer-siderar-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:00 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.6 percent to 3,515.45.  Mirgor SACIFYA (MIRG AF) rose 4.4 percent to 134 pesos, the
biggest gains six weeks. The Argentine producer of auto parts
has gained 17 percent since Feb. 14 as investors bet on a
positive outlook for car sales in the country this year, Alberto
Tarsia, a trader at Buenos Aires-based brokerage Debursa Soc. de
Bolsa SA, said today in a telephone interview.    Pampa Energia SA  (PAMP AF) fell for a third day, sliding
1.8 percent to 2.67 pesos. Raymond James & Associates Inc. put
its rating for Argentina’s largest energy holding company under
review.    Siderar SAIC  (ERAR AF) fell 1.1 percent to 32.30 pesos.
Argentina’s largest steel producer fell in line with markets in
Europe on concern that unrest in  Libya  will cause energy prices
to climb, slowing growth.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
